Final arguments are set to begin in the Air India bombing trial involving Sikh extremists in Canada.
Two suitcase bombs were checked onto Vancouver flights, leading to the deadliest terrorist act before 9/11.
The prosecution relies on witnesses, including a woman who worked for one of the accused and claimed they were in love.
The trial, heard by Justice Ian Bruce Josephson without a jury, is expected to conclude soon.
The accused, Ajaib Singh Bagri and Ripudaman Singh Malik, face charges related to the bombing that killed 329 people.
The prosecution alleges they were part of a group seeking revenge for a 1984 attack on a Sikh
